Key Match Events: Ben Stokes scored a century (108) with six fours and six sixes.
Chris Woakes and David Willey provided regular breakthroughs with the new ball.
Adil Rashid and Moeen Ali ensured Netherlands were bowled out before completing their overs.
Logan van Beek brought two crucial breakthroughs for the Netherlands.
Chris Woakes and Ben Stokes had a 129-run stand for the seventh wicket.
Teja Nidamanuru scored 41* for the Netherlands.
Netherlands lost their final five wickets for 16 runs, bowled out for 179.
Pre-Game Insights: Jos Buttler won the toss and elected to bat first.
Harry Brook and Gus Atkinson returned to the England side in place of Liam Livingstone and Mark Wood.
Scott Edwards mentioned he would have batted first as well but wasn't concerned about fielding first.
Teja Nidamanuru came in for Saqib Zulfiqar for the Netherlands.
Miscellaneous Highlights: England's innings saw 92 runs added off the last six overs.
England finished their first Powerplay period at a run rate of seven.
Dawid Malan hit 10 fours and two sixes in his innings.
Ben Stokes brought up his maiden Cricket World Cup ton in the 48th over.
